-- Indian shares gain for second day; IT stocks, Reliance lead
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Fri Dec 19, 2014 05:06AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Dec 19 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose for a second consecutive day on Friday, led by gains in IT stocks after global rival Accenture Plc raised its revenue forecast, while Reliance Industries rose on bets it will roll out its telecom services in the next few months.

Tata Consultancy Services <TCS.NS> provisionally rose 2.5 percent while Infosys <INFY.NS> ended 1.5 percent higher. Reliance Industries <RELI.NS> unofficially gained 2.3 percent.